article.headline: Liberty 84, High Point 81
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Leo Lightbourne had 24 points and 12 rebounds and made a layup with 1:02 to play to give Liberty an 84-81 victory against High Point on Tuesday night. The Flames (8-12, 6-3 Big South) trailed almost the entire night before Larry Blair's tip-in with 2:27 left gave them a 79-77 lead. After Akeem Scott's jumper tied it for High Point, Lightbourne broke the 10th tie of the night and Liberty held on for its 15th consecutive victory at the Vines Center against conference competition. Scott led High Point (10-11, 5-3) with 21 points and Danny Gathings had 15. The Panthers led 72-63 with 7:36 to go before Liberty used an 8-0 run to close the gap. Lightbourne had the last six points in the run, which ended with 5:36 left. After Lightbourne's go-ahead layup, Brian Woodson made 1 of 2 free throws for the Flames with 40 seconds left, and Woodson followed Scott's jumper by making two more from the line with 6 seconds left. Gathings missed a 3-point try at the end for High Point. David Dees and Blair added 16 points each for Liberty.
